---
source: tests/cli_help.rs
expression: stdout
---
Remove a block within a directory article

Usage: mf article block rm [OPTIONS] <ARTICLE> <BLOCK>

Arguments:
  <ARTICLE>  Article path (e.g. docs/my-article) or title
  <BLOCK>    Block filename (e.g. "02-notes.md"), stem (e.g. "02-notes"), or slug (e.g. "notes")

Options:
  -f, --force            Proceed despite safety checks: overwrite an existing target, or remove an
                         entity referenced by others
      --root <PATH>      Mind Repo root directory
      --config <PATH>    Config file path
  -y, --yes              Skip interactive confirmation prompt
      --dry-run          Preview changes without writing
  -v, --verbose...       Verbose output
  -q, --quiet            Silence non-error output
  -o, --output <FORMAT>  Output format [default: text] [possible values: text, json]
      --json             Shorthand for --output json
      --no-color         Disable colored output
  -p, --project <NAME>   Project name for project-scoped operations
  -h, --help             Print help
  -V, --version          Print version
